{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/particulate-matter-pollution-by-new-years-fireworks-5baad6efd540", "time": 1683002571.469034, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/particulate-matter-pollution-by-new-years-fireworks-5baad6efd540/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Particulate Matter pollution by New Year's fireworks | by Ignaz Wanders | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Particulate Matter pollution by New Year's fireworks", "description": "Each year at New Year tons of fireworks are launched into the atmosphere. It is no secret that fireworks is neither friendly to the environment, nor to people's health. A clear scientific report\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-019-42080-6", "anchor_text": "Greven, F.E., Vonk, J.M., Fischer, P. et al. Air pollution during New Year\u2019s fireworks and daily mortality in the Netherlands. Sci Rep 9, 5735 (2019) doi:10.1038/s41598\u2013019\u201342080\u20136", "paragraph_index": 1}], "all_paragraphs": ["Each year at New Year tons of fireworks are launched into the atmosphere. It is no secret that fireworks is neither friendly to the environment, nor to people's health.", "A clear scientific report about the negative impact of New Year's fireworks in the Netherlands is presented in a Nature article, which you can find here: Greven, F.E., Vonk, J.M., Fischer, P. et al. Air pollution during New Year\u2019s fireworks and daily mortality in the Netherlands. Sci Rep 9, 5735 (2019) doi:10.1038/s41598\u2013019\u201342080\u20136", "I thought it might be interesting to visualize the particulate matter (PM10) pollution in and around the Netherlands over the days before and after the New Year.", "In three earlier posts I outlined how we can do this using citizen science and open data:", "The result of the PM10 pollution is shown in this video, spanning a time range from 30 December 2019 00:00 to 3 January 2020 11:30. You can pause the video at any time to see the details of that particular moment.", "Unfortunately, the Luftdaten.info website is not as stable as before and quite some captured images had to be rejected because of server errors. This also resulted in a gap between 20:30 on 31 December and 06:00 on 1 January. Nevertheless, it is pretty clear how the PM10 concentration reaches a peak around New Year.", "We can also see this if we check the data of individual sensors. The peak around midnight is pretty obvious, and levels are incredibly high! (One sensor is just randomly picked from the city of Utrecht and the other from the city of Rotterdam.)", "In contrast, my own sensor, which is in Belgium in a region where fireworks are forbidden is shown below in the same time range. Levels are much lower, and no significant peak at midnight.", "There is a peak around 07:00 hours on 1 January, possibly due to the PM10 moving in from other areas, such as the Netherlands.", "The weather was not favorable: dense fog and low clouds, with no wind, so that traps pollution in low atmospheric layers.", "If fireworks were invented today it would never be legalized; it would fail safety, environmental, and health regulation.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F5baad6efd540&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fparticulate-matter-pollution-by-new-years-fireworks-5baad6efd540&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fparticulate-matter-pollution-by-new-years-fireworks-5baad6efd540&source=post_page---two_column_layout_na